==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Kaross
<hw>Ka*ross"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Native name.]</ety>
<def>A native garment or rug of skin sewed together in the form of a
square.</def> <mark>[South Africa]</mark></p>

<p><q>The wants of a native . . . are confined to a <qex>kaross</qex>
(skin cloak) or some pieces of cotton cloth.</q> <rj><qau>James
Bryce.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Karpholite</ent>⟦br⟧
